The paper introduces a new online learning framework that involves selecting a subset of actions with associated rewards and costs, while being constrained to an energy budget. This framework is applicable to several online learning problems where the environment changes over time. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), game theory (cs.GT), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
